html:
Etymology[edit]

Probably an incorrect Latinization of Ancient Greek χρυσανθής (khrusanthḗs) for scientific purposes.

Adjective[edit]

chrȳsanthus (feminine chrȳsantha, neuter chrȳsanthum); first/second-declension adjective

  1. (New Latin) having golden flowers

Declension[edit]

First/second-declension adjective.
